      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. and it's not just the signals. if you look at why the space program suddenly shifted focus so hard to the shuttle program and then basically stalled for decades, it smells like they hit a wall. like they saw something so impactful, something that changed the entire paradigm of human history, that they had to pivot everyone's attention away from the moon until they could process it. if we find evidence that the 1969 mission wasn't just about landing, but about a specific discovery of an ancient structure, we might be able to piece together why the \"inquiry\" into lunar geology was so heavily restricted afterward. what kind of specific declassified project names or budget redirects from that specific 1969-1972 window should we be looking for to track this kind of information suppression?",
